The Clean Technology Fund is offering
$85 million to fund renewable energy and so-called co-generation
energy projects in South Africa, it said in an advertisement in
Johannesburgâ€™s Business Day newspaper.  The Fund, whose capital is evenly managed in South Africa
by the International Finance Corporation and the African
Development Bank, is offering $50 million to fund wind or solar
projects and $35 million for co-generation plants, which use
waste energy and gases to generate power, the fund said in a
call for proposals.  The fund has a total of $150 million available to fund
projects in South Africa.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
